    "notes": "Updated 2026-05-09 from purchased-component datasheets. Sources: ISO-LP=Seagnol HPIISO-1064-10-H1-B-15-NE S/N 20240011006; PC-1=Seagnol MSPC-1064-211-F-10-105/125-5/130-5/130-15 S/N 25050300228; AMP-1 fiber=Coherent/Nufern SM-YDF-5/130-VIII lot 23-A4495-00-1D-05-02-02; ISO-HP-1=Seagnol CHPIISO-1064-01-H1-B-15-NE S/N 20240006; CIRC-1=Seagnol PICIR-1064-3-B-15-NE S/N 25041511; MFA-5/10=MFA-06-HI-10-1.5-2 S/N 25323050539; PC-2=Seagnol MSPC-1064-211-F-10-105/125-10/125-15 S/N 10032089; AMP-2 fiber=Coherent/Nufern LMA-YDF-10/125-9M lot 25-A4901-00-1B-11-01; MFA-10/30=MFA-06-SS-SS-1.5-2 S/N 25333998; AMP-3 fiber=Coherent/Nufern LMA-YDF-30/250-9M lot 21-D2144-00-2B-02. AMP-2 and AMP-3 clad_absorption_dB_per_m converted from datasheet 915 nm values to operating-wavelength (976 nm) equivalents using the ~3.0x ratio published by Coherent/Nufern across their LMA-YDF family (e.g. LMA-YDF-10/125-VIII: 1.6 dB/m at 915 nm, 4.8 dB/m at 976 nm). BPF-12, BPF-23, ISO-HP-2, and PC-3 still use literature estimates - no datasheets yet provided. CIRC-1 and CIRC-2 are used in double-pass mode with the FBGs (BPF-12, BPF-23) acting as the reflectors: each circulator is split into two entries (port 1->2 and port 2->3) placed around the FBG so the chain mirrors the physical layout. CIRC-1 port-pair losses 1.95 / 1.96 dB are the Seagnol datasheet tested values (S/N 25041511); CIRC-2 still uses 0.8 dB literature estimate for both passes - no datasheet yet."
  },
